author: Duncan Lindsay
title: Good news EastEnders fans – there’s a double episode tonight and it’s eventful!
text:
(Picture: BBC) There’s a double helping of EastEnders action in store for fans tonight as the BBC One soap fills in another of the episodes we lost out on due to pesky sports coverage – and there’s plenty going on in Walford during the hour of Tuesday night drama. 
We kick off with an episode centering around Ben Mitchell’s birthday but will the party go to plan as Jay Brown tries to give his best mate a night to remember? Abi Branning reckons that his ideal birthday gift might be Johnny Carter but is she right about there being sparks between them?
(Picture: BBC) Elsewhere, Denise Fox and Kush Kazemi grow closer at the Queen Vic quiz night – which sees a competitive Kim square up to a team of die-hard trivia fanatics. Lauren, meanwhile, is still harbouring thoughts for the man she met at a photocopier (swoon!) and as the second episode gets underway, she finds herself taking Whitney Carter on a night out just so she can bump into him.
(Picture: BBC) Back on the Square, oblivious Steven Beale is trying to build bridges with her dad Max, unaware that Lauren might be about to cheat on him.
The pressure is still on for Michelle Fowler but will Preston’s return ease or accelerate her stress? In other developments, Tina and Mick consider breaking the news to Sylvie that she might be going back into a home.
(Picture: BBC) Temptation, sexual tension, dilemmas, anguish…that’s a lot to squeeze into an hour!
EastEnders airs on Tuesday 21st March at 7:30pm and then again at 9pm on BBC One, with an hour of Holby City in between. What more could you want?
